    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## LINE-CS — Core Message Router\n\nInput from `entry-line`: one item per LINE text event:\n```\n{\n  event: { userId, text, eventId, replyToken },\n  settings: { ...all settings columns from Supabase... }\n}\n```\n\nPorted 1:1 from `netlify/functions/line-webhook.ts` (mihozip → scorpioliu0953/ai_customer_service).\n\nFlow:\n1. Dedup — insert processed_events(event_id); PK conflict → skip (duplicate retry)\n2. Read user_states[userId]\n3. Keyword detection → human handover (reply + agent push + flag is_human_mode)\n4. Human-mode + timeout check (inline lazy revert, matches original)\n5. is_ai_enabled gate\n6. GPT (chat / o-series / gpt-5 Responses) or Gemini\n7. Reply AI text\n\n**Only n8n credential needed = Supabase.** All LINE / OpenAI / Gemini calls are HTTP Request with keys read from the `settings` row (same as the original — keys live in DB so the dashboard can edit them).",
        "height": 620,
        "width": 560,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "sticky-overview",
      "name": "Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-1360, 220]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "row",
        "operation": "create",
        "tableId": "processed_events",
        "dataToSend": "defineBelow",
        "fieldsUi": {
          "fieldValues": [
            { "fieldId": "event_id", "fieldValue": "={{ $json.event.eventId }}" }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "dedup",
      "name": "Dedup (insert processed_events)",
